<p>I'm using Symfony 1.4 with Doctrine. I also use the sfDoctrineGuardPlugin and I want to use the 'auto logout' feature but it seems the AJAX requests on the site always overwrite the $this->lastRequest variable, therefore it is never going to reach the 'timeout' value and the user never going to be logoutted...</p>  <p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false"> <div class="snippet-code"> <pre class="snippet-code-js lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>if (false !== $timeout &amp;&amp; null !== $this - &gt; lastRequest &amp;&amp; time() - $this - &gt; lastRequest &gt;= $timeout) {   if ($this - &gt; options['logging']) {     $this - &gt; dispatcher - &gt; notify(new sfEvent($this, 'application.log', array('Automatic user logout due to timeout')));   }   $this - &gt; getGuardUser() - &gt; setOnline(0);   $this - &gt; getGuardUser() - &gt; save();   $this - &gt; setTimedOut();   $this - &gt; setAuthenticated(false); }</code></pre> </div> </div> </p>  <p>So how can I ban to AJAX to overwrite the $this->lastRequest parameter??</p>  <p>Many thanks!!!</p>